The President of the United States extends his best wishes to those observing Russia Day. He acknowledges the long-standing relationship between the American and Russian peoples. The President highlights the joint efforts of both nations in defeating fascism during World War II and the ongoing partnership, mutual respect, and friendship between them. He expresses pride in the new START Treaty and the joint efforts to reduce nuclear arsenals. Additionally, the President mentions the expansion of commercial and economic ties between the two countries. He recognizes the significant contribution of Americans with Russian origins to the national identity of the United States.